HEADWORD: Alembroth
<hw>A*lem"broth</hw> <pr>(-br⟦ocr⟧th)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Origin
uncertain.]</ety> <def>The <altname>salt of wisdom</altname> of the
alchemists, a double salt composed of the chlorides of ammonium and
mercury. It was formerly used as a stimulant.</def> <rj><au>Brande &
C.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

